data.title: University of Pennsylvania Athletics
data.meta_description: Chris Wynn (6) DB  - Career: Team Captain of the 2009 Ivy League champions ... Three-time First-Team All-Ivy ... Named to the 2009 Buck Buchanan Watch List
data.text:
Career: Team Captain of the 2009 Ivy League champions ... Three-time First-Team All-Ivy ... Named to the 2009 Buck Buchanan Watch List ... 2009 TSN Preseason Second Team All-American ... 2009 CDS Preseason Honorable Mention All-American ... 2008 TSN Third-Team All-American ... Holds the Penn record for career kick return yards with 1,236 ... Finished fifth all-time at Penn with 12 career interceptions, including one for a touchdown ... First Quaker in Ivy history with back-to-back seasons of five or more interceptions ... Led Ivy League in interceptions and passes defended as a junior ... Penn defense was No. 1 in the Ivy League in each of his last two seasons and No. 1 in the nation his senior season ... Finished career with 99 tackles and 39 passes defended.

2008: Appeared in all ten games for the Quakers as a starting cornerback ... TSN third team All-American ... First team All-Ivy ... Ivy League Special Teams Player of the Week (Oct. 13) ... Led the Quakers defense in interceptions and passes broken up, with five and nine, respectively ... Became first Quaker since start of Ivy play with back-to-back season with five or more interceptions ... Led the Ivy League in interceptions (ninth nationally) and passes defended ... Recorded 40 tackles (32 solo) on the season, good for sixth on the team ... Had six tackles each versus Columbia (10/15) and at Cornell (11/22) ... Returned 17 kickoffs for 443 yards (26.1 avg. ranked 14th in the nation) and 17 punts for 180 yards (10.6 avg.) as Pennâ€™s primary kick and punt returner ...Returned the opening kickoff for a touchdown at Georgetown (10/11) ... Trailed only Mike DiMaggio on the team with 623 all-purpose yards.

2007: First-team All-Ivy as a sophomore ... Played in all 10 games ... Finished season with five interceptions, which was good for third among Ivy players and 10th nationally ... Tied for second in Ivy play with 1.60 pass breakups per game ... Finished season with 28 tackles, including 17 solo ... Also returned 19 kickoffs for 436 yards, a 22.9 average ... Began season with four tackles and two interceptions against Lafayette (9/15) ... Collected five tackles at Columbia (10/13) ... Recorded four solo stops and a 12-yard interception against Yale (10/20) ... Returned an interception 25 yards and had two breakups at Brown (10/27) ... Four solo tackles and two pass breakups vs. Princeton (11/3) ... Had four tackles and two breakups at Harvard (11/10) ... Collected three stops and a breakup vs. Cornell (11/17).

2006: Played in nine games ... Had a kick return average of 27.7 yards per game ... Had three tackles against Lafayette (Sept. 16) ... Had two tackles against Villanova (Sept. 23) ... Recorded two tackles against Columbia (Oct. 14) Returned three kicks for 65 yards against Princeton (Nov. 4) ... Returned a kick-off 98 yards for a touchdown - the fourth-longest return in Penn history - against Brown ... Also had two tackles versus the Bears (Oct. 28).

Hunterdon Central HS: Three-sport athlete in football, lacrosse and track ... Named all-state, all-conference and all-area as a senior ... Two-time county player of the year, in 2004 and 2005 ... Helped his lacrosse team to a state title in 2005.
